sting

Annotation Type Injectable


  • @Target(value=TYPE)
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Documented
public @interface Injectable
    Identifies an injectable type. Types annotated with this are expected to be created by an injector. The type must be concrete and must have a single package-access constructor. The constructor can accept zero or more dependencies as arguments. Optional Dependencies

    A non-primitive parameter can be marked as optional by annotating it with the @Nullable annotation. If the injector can not find a value to satisfy the dependency then the injector may pass null for the parameter.

    Qualified Dependencies

    A parameter may can also be annotated with the @ServiceSpec annotation with the qualifier parameter specified. To satisfy the dependency the provided value must be declared with the same qualifier.

    Circular Dependencies

    Circular dependencies are disallowed by the injector and are rejected during the compilation phase. The developer can break the circular dependency by injecting Supplier<OtherType> instead of OtherType and then calling get() on the supplier when access to the dependency is needed.

    See Also:
    @Dependency, Supplier

      • types

        public abstract Class<?>[] types
        The types of dependency that this binding can satisfy. By default the binding will match the type that is annotated. If specified, the binding will only match the types specified and every type must be assignable from the type that is annotated.
        Returns:
        the types of dependency that this binding can satisfy.

        void.class
